title: Attack on Sindh Rangers: Personnel injured, seven terrorists neutralised
text:
Terrorists planning attacks on police officials arrested in Karachi 
KARACHI: Six terrorists were gunned down on early Friday morning after militants ambushed paramilitary forces at Kathore super-highway, informed Ranger`s spokesperson. 
The spox said that as many as 25 Rangers` personnel were returning to Karachi from Sehwan in five vehicles when a terror group attacked them. A heavy cross-fire ensued immediately. The paramilitary forces cordoned off the area and demanded contingents from Karachi headquarters. 
In the exchange of fire, one personnel were injured while six terrorists were shot dead. 
The identities of the miscreants were not yet informed by the authorities, however, the deceased would be shifted to a hospital for medico-legal formalities. 0 0 Attack on Sindh Rangers: Personnel injured, seven terrorists neutralised was posted in pakistan of Geo TV - https://www.geo.tv on February 17, 2017 and was last updated on February 17, 2017.
